922
01:01:24,244 --> 01:01:26,287
(eerie rumbling)

923
01:01:36,339 --> 01:01:39,175
~ ~

924
01:01:43,554 --> 01:01:45,890
(hammering)

925
01:01:52,272 --> 01:01:55,275
(hammering continuing)

926
01:01:58,861 --> 01:02:00,154
Excuse me, Mr. Morgan.

927
01:02:00,530 --> 01:02:03,575
I was wondering if you'd have
a moment to speak with me.

928
01:02:03,616 --> 01:02:04,617
My name's Rachel Keller.

929
01:02:04,659 --> 01:02:06,244
I'm a writer with
the "Seattle P.I."

930
01:02:06,286 --> 01:02:08,204
You want to know
about the horses.

931
01:02:10,790 --> 01:02:11,874
I didn't mean to...

932
01:02:11,916 --> 01:02:14,752
It's just I wasn't able to
find a number to reach you.

933
01:02:14,794 --> 01:02:17,755
Every now and then,
a writer comes along...

934
01:02:17,797 --> 01:02:19,632
heard about what happened.

935
01:02:19,632 --> 01:02:23,094
What's left to write about,
though, I don't know.

936
01:02:23,136 --> 01:02:25,763
I was hoping you had
just a few minutes.

937
01:02:25,805 --> 01:02:29,767
Well, work never ends
around here, really...

938
01:02:29,809 --> 01:02:32,020
but I guess I got a few.

939
01:02:32,061 --> 01:02:35,189
So, what is it
you're writing, miss?

940
01:02:35,732 --> 01:02:36,816
About horses in general

941
01:02:36,858 --> 01:02:38,067
or just those that go strange?

942
01:02:38,109 --> 01:02:40,737
I read you had
to put so many down.

943
01:02:40,778 --> 01:02:42,739
Most put themselves down.

944
01:02:42,780 --> 01:02:44,073
They drowned.

945
01:02:44,115 --> 01:02:45,241
How'd they get out?

946
01:02:45,283 --> 01:02:46,576
They just broke

947
01:02:46,618 --> 01:02:49,621
through the fences
and ran to the shore.

948
01:02:49,662 --> 01:02:51,247
So, they went crazy?

949
01:02:51,289 --> 01:02:53,374
It would seem so, yes...

950
01:02:53,499 --> 01:02:56,753
or maybe they just sense things
before we do.

951
01:02:58,838 --> 01:03:01,799
So, where are your horses now?

952
01:03:03,843 --> 01:03:05,386
I don't breed anymore.

953
01:03:05,470 --> 01:03:07,764
I guess you wouldn't...

954
01:03:07,805 --> 01:03:10,183
not after what happened.

955
01:03:10,224 --> 01:03:14,687
That must've been hard...
on both of you...

956
01:03:14,729 --> 01:03:17,774
you and your wife.

957
01:03:17,815 --> 01:03:20,276
(thunder rumbling)

958
01:03:20,318 --> 01:03:24,948
I'm sorry, miss,
what's your name again?

959
01:03:24,989 --> 01:03:26,366
Rachel.

960
01:03:26,366 --> 01:03:27,867
Well, Rachel...

961
01:03:27,867 --> 01:03:31,204
you want to tell me what's
really on your mind?

962
01:03:34,749 --> 01:03:36,709
Do you know what this is?

963
01:03:39,212 --> 01:03:41,172
I think it's a message...

964
01:03:41,214 --> 01:03:43,216
from your wife.

965
01:03:45,009 --> 01:03:46,177
Anna's on this tape.

966
01:03:46,219 --> 01:03:47,887
She's right there in that room.

967
01:03:47,929 --> 01:03:51,391
You can see the lighthouse,
the horses...

968
01:03:53,393 --> 01:03:55,019
Where'd you get that?

969
01:03:55,061 --> 01:03:56,896
Shelter Mountain Inn.

970
01:03:58,940 --> 01:04:00,817
Is that the only one?

971
01:04:02,902 --> 01:04:05,488
I made a copy.

972
01:04:07,615 --> 01:04:09,284
(sighs)

973
01:04:11,744 --> 01:04:15,707
I've got a lot of work
to do today...

974
01:04:15,748 --> 01:04:17,750
a lot of acres out there.

975
01:04:17,792 --> 01:04:21,045
Minute I think I'm done
with one thing...

976
01:04:23,423 --> 01:04:27,051
...another thing needs fixing.

977
01:04:27,093 --> 01:04:29,304
You don't want to see this tape?

978
01:04:29,345 --> 01:04:31,055
You're not even curious?

979
01:04:31,097 --> 01:04:32,724
Curious?

980
01:04:32,765 --> 01:04:35,101
No. I don't think so.

981
01:04:37,270 --> 01:04:38,605
Mr. Morgan...

982
01:04:38,605 --> 01:04:39,772
I can't help you.

983
01:04:41,816 --> 01:04:43,484
Where's your daughter?

984
01:04:43,610 --> 01:04:45,236
Maybe she could help...

985
01:04:45,278 --> 01:04:47,614
I don't have a daughter.

986
01:04:47,614 --> 01:04:48,865
Excuse me?

987
01:04:48,907 --> 01:04:50,950
What is it with reporters?

988
01:04:50,992 --> 01:04:53,328
You take one person's tragedy

989
01:04:53,369 --> 01:04:56,497
and force the world
to experience it...

990
01:04:56,623 --> 01:04:59,918
spread it like sickness.

991
01:04:59,959 --> 01:05:01,002
Mr. Morgan...

992
01:05:01,044 --> 01:05:02,378
Tell me, miss...

993
01:05:02,420 --> 01:05:04,964
what is it you think you know?

994
01:05:07,091 --> 01:05:09,677
Then leave it alone.

995
01:05:14,807 --> 01:05:15,808
(slams)

996
01:05:15,850 --> 01:05:18,144
(sighs)

997
01:05:22,649 --> 01:05:24,275
(sighs)

