NOAH:
Rachel!

1393
01:33:29,752 --> 01:33:34,007
Rachel, the sun's set!

1394
01:33:34,048 --> 01:33:35,216
The sun has set!

1395
01:33:35,258 --> 01:33:36,467
It's past sunset.

1396
01:33:36,509 --> 01:33:37,635
Do you hear me?

1397
01:33:37,677 --> 01:33:40,346
It's past sunset!

1398
01:33:44,309 --> 01:33:47,103
Rachel?

1399
01:33:56,529 --> 01:33:58,531
Rachel?

1400
01:34:03,578 --> 01:34:06,497
Rachel, are you there?

1401
01:34:06,539 --> 01:34:08,541
(shivering)

1402
01:34:11,544 --> 01:34:13,212
I'm here.

1403
01:34:13,254 --> 01:34:15,882
(frogs croaking)

1404
01:34:15,924 --> 01:34:18,343
(speaking indistinctly)

1405
01:34:25,808 --> 01:34:27,977
(speaking indistinctly)

1406
01:34:30,313 --> 01:34:32,649
They're going to bury her
next week.

1407
01:34:36,486 --> 01:34:38,154
It's over.

1408
01:34:45,662 --> 01:34:47,580
You okay?

1409
01:34:47,580 --> 01:34:53,211
She wanted that child
more than anything in the world.

1410
01:34:53,253 --> 01:34:56,339
How could she have done that?

1411
01:34:59,550 --> 01:35:02,553
She just wanted to be heard.

1412
01:35:05,890 --> 01:35:09,894
Sometimes children...

1413
01:35:09,936 --> 01:35:14,065
yell or cry or draw pictures.

1414
01:35:14,107 --> 01:35:17,110
~ ~

1415
01:35:27,036 --> 01:35:29,038
I want to go home.

1416
01:35:32,125 --> 01:35:35,086
~ ~

1417
01:35:44,137 --> 01:35:47,807
I can't imagine being stuck
down a well all alone like that.

1418
01:35:49,475 --> 01:35:51,811
How long could you survive?

1419
01:35:58,484 --> 01:36:00,069
Seven days.

1420
01:36:06,117 --> 01:36:09,621
You could survive
for seven days.

1421
01:36:16,711 --> 01:36:19,714
~ ~

1422
01:36:22,717 --> 01:36:25,720
(rain falling)

1423
01:36:35,730 --> 01:36:38,816
~ ~

1424
01:36:38,858 --> 01:36:41,194
Come on.

1425
01:36:41,236 --> 01:36:43,071
Hey.

1426
01:36:48,785 --> 01:36:51,788
~ ~

1427
01:37:01,756 --> 01:37:04,759
~ ~

1428
01:37:14,561 --> 01:37:18,606
~ ~

1429
01:37:18,648 --> 01:37:21,609
Why don't you just
call me sometime?

1430
01:37:21,651 --> 01:37:23,611
Unless you're renting a movie.

1431
01:37:23,653 --> 01:37:25,280
(chuckles)

1432
01:37:25,321 --> 01:37:26,614
(sighs)

1433
01:37:26,656 --> 01:37:28,658
Call me tomorrow...

1434
01:37:32,620 --> 01:37:34,956
...and the day after that.

1435
01:37:44,632 --> 01:37:46,634
~ ~

1436
01:37:54,893 --> 01:37:57,896
~ ~

1437
01:38:07,196 --> 01:38:09,198
(murmurs)

1438
01:38:16,289 --> 01:38:18,333
Rachel?

1439
01:38:18,374 --> 01:38:21,336
Hmm?

1440
01:38:21,377 --> 01:38:24,339
What time is it?

1441
01:38:24,380 --> 01:38:27,342
It's either really late
or really early...

1442
01:38:27,383 --> 01:38:30,678
depending on how you look at it.

1443
01:38:30,720 --> 01:38:33,181
Don't you have to be at work?

1444
01:38:33,222 --> 01:38:36,184
Not today.

1445
01:38:40,563 --> 01:38:43,524
What happened to the girl?

1446
01:38:43,650 --> 01:38:45,526
Samara?

1447
01:38:45,652 --> 01:38:47,528
Is that her name?

1448
01:38:47,570 --> 01:38:48,863
Mm-hmm.

1449
01:38:48,905 --> 01:38:51,115
Is she still in the dark place?

1450
01:38:51,157 --> 01:38:52,450
No.

1451
01:38:52,492 --> 01:38:55,161
We set her free.

1452
01:38:57,163 --> 01:38:59,165
You helped her?

1453
01:38:59,165 --> 01:39:00,792
Yeah.

1454
01:39:00,833 --> 01:39:02,835
Why did you do that?

1455
01:39:05,004 --> 01:39:06,631
What's wrong, honey?

1456
01:39:06,673 --> 01:39:08,549
You weren't supposed
to help her.

1457
01:39:08,591 --> 01:39:10,260
It's okay now.

1458
01:39:10,301 --> 01:39:12,804
She's not going to hurt you.

1459
01:39:12,845 --> 01:39:14,305
She...

1460
01:39:20,395 --> 01:39:22,063
Don't you understand, Rachel?

1461
01:39:24,107 --> 01:39:26,442
She never sleeps.

1462
01:39:40,123 --> 01:39:43,167
(TVstatic blaring)

1463
01:39:53,052 --> 01:39:55,847
(static continuing)

1464
01:40:04,564 --> 01:40:07,191
(static stops)

1465
01:40:10,737 --> 01:40:13,740
(static hissing)

1466
01:40:19,662 --> 01:40:23,124
(ringing)

1467
01:40:23,166 --> 01:40:24,125
(ringing through)

1468
01:40:24,167 --> 01:40:27,128
Pick up the phone, Noah.

1469
01:40:27,170 --> 01:40:30,423
Come on, pick up.

1470
01:40:32,425 --> 01:40:34,802
(phone ringing)

1471
01:40:34,844 --> 01:40:37,430
(static hissing)

1472
01:40:45,438 --> 01:40:47,649
(ringing continuing)

1473
01:40:47,732 --> 01:40:50,610
~ ~

1474
01:40:57,283 --> 01:40:58,868
(ringing continuing)

1475
01:40:58,910 --> 01:41:01,913
(eerie whirring)

1476
01:41:11,422 --> 01:41:13,633
(ringing continuing)

1477
01:41:13,675 --> 01:41:16,678
(tires squealing)

1478
01:41:16,761 --> 01:41:19,055
RACHEL:
Come on, Noah!

1479
01:41:19,097 --> 01:41:21,391
Pick up the goddamn phone!

1480
01:41:21,432 --> 01:41:22,684
(horn honking)

1481
01:41:22,767 --> 01:41:26,020
(tires squealing)

1482
01:41:26,062 --> 01:41:28,314
(trickling)

1483
01:41:28,356 --> 01:41:30,858
(phone ringing)

1484
01:41:36,906 --> 01:41:39,367
(gasping)

1485
01:41:39,409 --> 01:41:41,786
(ringing continuing)

1486
01:41:51,504 --> 01:41:52,714
(gasping)

1487
01:41:52,797 --> 01:41:57,010
(grunting)

1488
01:42:06,185 --> 01:42:08,187
(ringing continuing)

1489
01:42:08,187 --> 01:42:09,355
(grunting)

1490
01:42:14,193 --> 01:42:15,862
(screaming)

1491
01:42:15,904 --> 01:42:17,614
(static blaring)

1492
01:42:17,655 --> 01:42:20,116
(brakes squealing)

1493
01:42:20,158 --> 01:42:22,952
(panting)

1494
01:42:22,994 --> 01:42:25,747
~ ~

1495
01:42:25,788 --> 01:42:27,123
Come on!

1496
01:42:35,882 --> 01:42:38,384
(phone ringing)

1497
01:42:38,426 --> 01:42:40,762
(static hissing)

1498
01:42:40,803 --> 01:42:43,765
(ringing continuing)

1499
01:42:43,806 --> 01:42:46,476
(ringing through)

1500
01:42:56,486 --> 01:42:59,489
(static hissing continues)

1501
01:43:01,908 --> 01:43:04,911
(glass crunching)

1502
01:43:12,001 --> 01:43:14,045
(hissing continues)

1503
01:43:23,930 --> 01:43:26,975
(sighs)

1504
01:43:33,106 --> 01:43:34,691
(screaming)

1505
01:43:34,732 --> 01:43:36,693
(screaming echoing)

1506
01:43:36,734 --> 01:43:38,695
(panting and crying)

1507
01:43:38,736 --> 01:43:41,239
(thud)

1508
01:43:41,281 --> 01:43:44,075
(elevator whirring)

1509
01:43:54,043 --> 01:43:56,546
(elevator whirring)

1510
01:44:02,510 --> 01:44:04,846
(sobbing)

1511
01:44:14,522 --> 01:44:16,232
Go to your room!

1512
01:44:16,274 --> 01:44:17,692
Now!

1513
01:44:23,072 --> 01:44:24,365
(breathing anxiously)

1514
01:44:24,407 --> 01:44:25,825
What do you want?

1515
01:44:25,825 --> 01:44:28,119
What do you want?!

1516
01:44:28,161 --> 01:44:30,121
What do you want from me?

1517
01:44:30,163 --> 01:44:32,165
(crying)

1518
01:44:38,504 --> 01:44:40,465
(sobbing)

1519
01:44:47,597 --> 01:44:50,099
Why not me?

1520
01:44:52,769 --> 01:44:55,271
What did I do that he didn't?

1521
01:44:58,775 --> 01:45:00,777
(crying stops)

1522
01:45:08,660 --> 01:45:10,912
(fire crackling)

1523
01:45:15,833 --> 01:45:17,835
~ ~

1524
01:45:27,136 --> 01:45:31,182
(echoing):
She just wanted to be heard.

1525
01:45:31,224 --> 01:45:34,435
He wants me to go away.

1526
01:45:34,477 --> 01:45:36,896
My wife was not supposed
to have a child!

1527
01:45:36,896 --> 01:45:38,398
ANNA:
All I ever wanted was you.

1528
01:45:38,398 --> 01:45:40,066
AIDAN:
Don't you understand, Rachel?

1529
01:45:40,108 --> 01:45:42,068
But he doesn't know.

1530
01:45:42,068 --> 01:45:43,486
She never sleeps.

1531
01:45:43,528 --> 01:45:45,071
MORGAN:
You take one person's tragedy

1532
01:45:45,113 --> 01:45:48,283
and force the world
to experience it.

1533
01:45:48,324 --> 01:45:49,867
You spread it like sickness.

1534
01:45:49,909 --> 01:45:52,537
MAN:
You don't want to hurt anyone.

1535
01:45:52,579 --> 01:45:54,205
But I do.

1536
01:45:55,123 --> 01:45:58,459
And I'm sorry.

1537
01:45:58,501 --> 01:46:01,921
It won't stop.

1538
01:46:04,924 --> 01:46:07,468
RACHEL:
I made a copy.

1539
01:46:09,262 --> 01:46:11,764
Push it in.

1540
01:46:11,764 --> 01:46:13,766
"Play."

1541
01:46:13,808 --> 01:46:15,143
Push.

1542
01:46:19,606 --> 01:46:22,567
(high-pitched
electronic whining)

1543
01:46:22,609 --> 01:46:26,529
It's going to keep killing,
isn't it?

1544
01:46:26,613 --> 01:46:28,823
She'll never stop.

1545
01:46:28,865 --> 01:46:30,283
Don't worry, sweetie.

1546
01:46:30,325 --> 01:46:33,578
You're going to be okay.

1547
01:46:38,917 --> 01:46:42,462
What about the person
we show it to?

1548
01:46:42,503 --> 01:46:44,714
What happens to them?

1549
01:46:51,304 --> 01:46:54,265
(static hissing)

1550
01:46:54,307 --> 01:46:56,267
(static blaring)

1551
01:54:24,048 --> 01:54:26,009
(music box playing)

1552
01:54:26,050 --> 01:54:30,471
CHILD:
~ Here we go ~

1553
01:54:30,555 --> 01:54:35,685
~ The world is spinning ~

1554
01:54:35,727 --> 01:54:40,023
~ When it stops ~

1555
01:54:40,064 --> 01:54:45,987
~ It's just beginning ~

1556
01:54:47,947 --> 01:54:52,493
~ Sun comes up ~

1557
01:54:52,619 --> 01:54:57,916
~ We laugh and we cry ~

1558
01:54:57,957 --> 01:55:02,295
~ Sun goes down ~

1559
01:55:02,337 --> 01:55:05,423
~ And then we all die. ~

